A man, who was caught with heroin with a street value of R50 million, pleaded guilty to possession of drugs on Friday. According to Hawks spokesman, Lt Dineo Sekgotodi, Isaac Mtashini (50) was sentenced to five years&#8217; imprisonment or a R50 000 fine. He also received a five-year suspended sentence on condition he does not commit a similar offence.Read more here: DRUG BUST ARTICLESIsaac Mtashini (50) pleaded guilty to possession of drugs.